io.mosip.registration.util.mastersync

Class MetaDataUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.mosip.registration.util.mastersync.MetaDataUtils

  • @Component
public class MetaDataUtils
extends Object
    MetaDataUtils class provide methods to copy values from DTO to entity along with that it create some meta data which is required before an entity to be saved into database.

    1.0.0
    Author:
    Sreekar Chukka

        public static <S,D extends RegistrationCommonFields> D setUpdateMetaData(S source,
                                                                         D destination,
                                                                         Boolean mapNullvalues)
        This method takes source object like an DTO and a class which must extends RegistrationCommonFields and map all values from DTO object to the destination object and return it.
        Type Parameters:
        S - the generic type
        D - the generic type
        Parameters:
        source - is the source
        destination - is the destination
        mapNullvalues - if marked as false then field inside source which are null will not be mapped into destination
        Returns:
        an entity class which extends RegistrationCommonFields
        Throws:
        io.mosip.kernel.core.dataaccess.exception.DataAccessLayerException - if any error occurs while mapping values
